@autorefoff
  File
@box 2 21 13
   @{"New..." link %mnew}          ^N   Creates new files, folders, groups and links
   @{"Open..." link %mopen}         ^O   Opens a file, folder etc.
   @{"Search..." link %mfind}       ^F   Starts the external file finder
   @{"Show Info..." link %minfo}    ^I   Shows informations about the selectet object(s)
 @{G}---------------------@{g}
   @{"Close" link %mclose}           ^H   Closes the current directory
   @{"View..." link %mshow}         ^Z   View a file with the appropriate application
   @{"Print..." link %mprint}        ^P   Print a file with the appropriate application
   @{"Save Group" link %msavegroup}      ^S   Save changes in the current object group
 @{G}---------------------@{g}
   @{"Format Disk..." link %mformat}       Format a floppy disk
 @{G}---------------------@{g}
   @{"Quit" link %mquit}            ^Q   Leave Thing or perform a shut-down
@autorefon

This menu contains functions to handle files or folders. Please note that
there must be at least one registered application for viewing or printing
files!

The function 'Search...' is only available, if there is an external file
finder specified in the page 'System' of the 'Setup' dialog box. File
finders may be external programs as well as accessories.

Is Thing running as a shell under MagiC!2, there is no 'Quit' entry,
because MagiC!2 would start Thing again automatically -- so a 'Quit' would
not work with MagiC!2.

Is Thing running as a shell Under MagiC!3, 'Shut Down' can be found to
perform a 'shut-down'.
@endnode

