@node %mnew "File - New..."
@prev %mnew
@toc "Menu commands"
@autorefoff
File - New...                                                         Thing
@line 1 75 0 0 7
@autorefon

This function is used to create new files, folders, object groups or links.

@{B}Objekt type:@{b} This option determines the desired object type. Folders
  can only be created in the current directory. If there is no directory
  window activ, the types 'File' and 'Folder' are not selectable.

If the object type 'Object group' was selected, the following entries
appear:

@{B}Group file:@{b} The name to save the group file. Thing locates the
  group file in the same directory the configuration files and icons are
  stored. Group files can subsequently be moved so long as the extender
  '.GRP' isn't changed.

@{B}Title:@{b} Here a name for the group is entered and used as the window
  title. If the field is left empty, the file name will be used as title.

@{B}Save changes automatically:@{b} If this option is set, all changes of
  the group will be saved immediatly. Otherwise, a leading '*' will be
  added to the window title.

@{B}Put icon to the desktop:@{b} A new file icon for the group will be
  created on the desktop.
@endnode

